"InstructionsTitle" = "Finder Instructions";
"InstructionsIntro" = "Features:\nFinder is a local network camera and gallery app that lets you easily view, upload, download, and manage your phone's photos on your computer browser via Wi-Fi, without needing a cable.";
"InstructionsSteps" = "Usage Steps:\n1. Connect to same Wi-Fi: Ensure your phone and computer are on the same local network.\n2. Enable Web Gallery Service: Turn on the switch in the main interface. Once started, a URL will appear.\n3. Browser Access: Enter the URL in your computer browser. You can long-press the URL on your phone to copy it.\n4. Real-time Sync: Click 'Take Photo' in the App. The photo will instantly appear in the web gallery.\n5. Web Operations: Download original photos, drag and drop to upload, or delete old photos directly from the browser.\n6. Local Preview: Click 'Local Preview' in the App to manage and view all photos natively.";
"InstructionsEnd" = "Enjoy using Finder!";
